The paper discusses security and privacy issues in the context of connected vehicles and intelligent transportation systems, which are primarily related to computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of Big Data and the proposed system model also suggest a connection to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes security requirements and discusses open research challenges, which are typical of software engineering (cs.SE).
